[SN]TITLE[SN]
Rio Olympics 2016: Oleg Verniaiev wins parallel bars gold for Ukraine

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Ukraine's Oleg Verniaiev won Olympic gold on the parallel bars in Rio after narrowly missing out on the all-around title.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 22-year-old won with a total of 16.041, as USA's Danell Leyva claimed silver and Russia's David Belyavskiy took bronze.
World champion You Hao finished eighth, as China left the Rio gymnastics competition without a title.
It was the first time they have not won gold in the sport since 1980.
China boycotted the Moscow Games that year.
Verniaiev missed out on the all-around title by just 0.101 points after hopping forward when dismounting the high bar.
